  128  2026-04-16 10:01  cat > ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/coding-agent/SKILL.md << 'SKILL'\n---\nname: coding-agent\ndescription: Delegate complex coding tasks to Claude Code CLI. Use for building features, debugging, refactoring, running tests, and PR reviews on INFERA projects.\n---\n\n# Coding Agent Delegation\n\nWhen Rateb asks for a coding task (build, fix, debug, refactor, test), delegate to Claude Code via the bash tool.\n\n## IMPORTANT: Always use the bash tool, NEVER use sessions_spawn or ACP.\n\n## How to launch Claude Code\n\nFor short tasks (< 5 min):\n```\nbash workdir:~/Projects/infera-green command:"claude --print --permission-mode bypassPermissions 'YOUR TASK HERE'"\n```\n\nFor long tasks (> 5 min), run in background:\n```\nbash workdir:~/Projects/infera-green background:true command:"claude --print --permission-mode bypassPermissions 'YOUR TASK HERE. When completely finished, run: openclaw system event --text \"Done: BRIEF SUMMARY\" --mode now'"\n```\n\n## Quick test command\n```\nbash workdir:~/Projects command:"claude --print --permission-mode bypassPermissions 'Write a Python script that prints bonjour and run it'"\n```\n\n## Rules\n\n- Use the `bash` tool to invoke `claude` CLI. Do NOT use sessions_spawn, ACP, or any other method.\n- Default project directory: ~/Projects/infera-green\n- NEVER run Claude Code in ~/.openclaw/\n- Tell Rateb when you start a task and when it finishes.\n- For simple one-liner edits, use the edit tool directly — don't spawn Claude Code for trivial stuff.\n- If Claude Code is not available, fall back to writing code directly with the write/edit tools.\nSKILL
